-- Regal Entertainment Reaches Deal With Disney to Show ‘Iron Man’
-- B y   M i c h a e l   W h i t e
-- 2013-04-25T21:31:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-25/regal-entertainment-reaches-deal-with-disney-to-show-iron-man-.html
Regal Entertainment Group (RGC) , the
largest U.S. cinema chain, reached a revenue-sharing agreement
with  Walt Disney Co. (DIS) , clearing the way for its theaters to show
“ Iron Man  3.”  Regal, based in Knoxville, Tennessee, announced the
agreement today in an e-mailed statement. The company is taking
steps to begin accepting online orders at its Regal, United
Artists and Edwards theaters, according to the statement. AMC
Entertainment Holdings reached an agreement with Disney earlier
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Michael White in Los Angeles at 
